Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks. Pick the @rosemary{½}(roughly chopped, stalks discarded) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @Panko Breadcrumbs{25%g} with half the garlic and half the rosemary. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and cook, stirring regularly, until golden brown, ~{2-3%mins}. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside but don't wash up the pan.

Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the @Linda McCartney Sausages{6} and cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%mins}. Transfer the sausages to a #chopping board{}. Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle more @oil{} if needed. Add the shallot and red pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and starting to turn brown, ~{3-4%mins}. Add the @Smoked Paprika{1%tsp}, remaining garlic and rosemary and cook, stirring, for a further ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Tomatoes{1}(finely chopped) and @Tomato Puree{30%g} to the pan, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add the @Sugar{}(see ingredients for amount) and bring to a simmer. Lower the heat and cook until thick and tomatoey, ~{10-12%mins}. TIP Add a splash of water if too thick. While the sauce cooks, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{12%mins}.

While the pasta is cooking, cut the sausages widthways into roughly 2cm thick rounds. About ~{5%minutes} before everything is ready, add the sausages to the sauce and cook until everything is piping hot. Taste and season the sauce with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and add a further splash of water if you need to.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain it in a #colander{} and add to the sauce. Mix well until everything is evenly coated. Divide between plates and top with the herby garlicky breadcrumbs. Enjoy!